conversation between girls!

68
00:04:04,811 --> 00:04:07,939
Oh really. Then you admit
you averted your eyes.

69
00:04:08,014 --> 00:04:08,878
Hey...

70
00:04:08,982 --> 00:04:12,918
That's what they call ignoring,
you know. Ig-nor-ing!

71
00:04:13,019 --> 00:04:14,748
I even waved to you.

72
00:04:14,854 --> 00:04:18,483
Fine then, I was ignoring you!
But even if I spoke up...

73
00:04:18,558 --> 00:04:20,492
...you'd probably make some
really annoyed face at me!

74
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:24,360
No, I wouldn't! First off, we
were talking about otaku fashion...

75
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:25,865
...so I wanted you to come over!

76
00:04:25,865 --> 00:04:26,832
No thanks!

77
00:04:26,899 --> 00:04:27,797
Um...

78
00:04:27,867 --> 00:04:31,564
You know, everyone's already
aware that my boyfriend's an otaku.

79
00:04:31,738 --> 00:04:34,332
And they know I frequent Genshiken!

80
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:37,907
Do not let it go to your head.

81
00:04:37,977 --> 00:04:41,378
No amount of time will
make you an otaku...

82
00:04:41,447 --> 00:04:43,349
...which proves you
are from another planet.

83
00:04:43,349 --> 00:04:44,441
Shut up.

84
00:04:44,651 --> 00:04:47,017
Someday you will break up with Kohsaka.

85
00:04:47,787 --> 00:04:49,516
You piss me off, otaku!

86
00:04:49,589 --> 00:04:53,389
I am from the planet Otaku.

87
00:04:53,459 --> 00:04:54,627
I come in peace.

88
00:04:54,627 --> 00:04:56,857
I come in peace.
Otaku, otaku, otaku, otaku, otaku!

89
00:05:01,868 --> 00:05:02,766
Your glasses.

90
00:05:08,107 --> 00:05:10,268
They're square!

91
00:05:10,643 --> 00:05:11,667
You only just noticed?

92
00:05:12,512 --> 00:05:13,843
S-square!

93
00:05:17,016 --> 00:05:20,645
So, what? You're
suddenly trying for style?

94
00:05:20,953 --> 00:05:26,050
Well, it was a change, and I was
starting to need a new prescription.

95
00:05:26,392 --> 00:05:27,381
Do they suck?

96
00:05:27,627 --> 00:05:32,087
Huh? They don't suck... but it's like...

97
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:35,965
Your laughing suggests they suck.

98
00:05:36,035 --> 00:05:39,605
It's your clothes. I was
talking about it with Ogiue too.

99
00:05:39,605 --> 00:05:40,435
Oh, right.

100
00:05:40,506 --> 00:05:41,973
Do none of you care?

101
00:05:42,575 --> 00:05:45,544
That's what they call
otaku fashion, huh?

102
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:47,779
Are you cool with hearing that?

103
00:05:48,514 --> 00:05:49,913
Does it not make any difference?

104
00:05:50,416 --> 00:05:54,443
Well, it's like, no, I don't care.
And I have no taste for it.

105
00:05:54,587 --> 00:05:55,918
Not to mention money.

106
00:05:56,422 --> 00:05:59,983
Suddenly you get defensive?
Does it sting that badly?

107
00:06:00,626 --> 00:06:03,720
An otaku accepts no
challenge he can't win.

108
00:06:04,397 --> 00:06:09,027
About that. Don't you two think it's
more indecent to dress stylishly?

109
00:06:09,135 --> 00:06:11,000
"We don't bother."

110
00:06:11,537 --> 00:06:12,972
"We're hardcore otaku!"

111
00:06:12,972 --> 00:06:15,270
Like a reverse superiority complex...

112
00:06:15,641 --> 00:06:16,835
Easy for you to say.

113
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:17,771
Yeah.

114
00:06:18,444 --> 00:06:22,346
Kohsaka buys both clothes
and games, and he manages.

115
00:06:22,882 --> 00:06:23,940
Kohsaka's...

116
00:06:24,016 --> 00:06:26,348
True, he has different
substance and taste.

117
00:06:27,820 --> 00:06:30,550
But it's okay even
if you have bad taste.

118
00:06:30,823 --> 00:06:33,553
What's bad is giving up
and being all defiant.

119
00:06:33,926 --> 00:06:38,363
You say it's outside your specialty
and don't even try to show interest.

120
00:06:38,431 --> 00:06:41,161
I think that's the
biggest problem with otaku.

121
00:06:42,135 --> 00:06:42,863
Huh?

122
00:06:47,073 --> 00:06:48,700
S-square!

123
00:06:48,841 --> 00:06:50,968
Just can't get past that, huh?

124
00:06:57,884 --> 00:07:00,148
What am I doing in a place like this?

125
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:05,156
Well, I wanted a new
jacket and pants at least.

126
00:07:05,892 --> 00:07:07,086
That's all this is.

127
00:07:14,467 --> 00:07:16,958
I've never been in a store like that.

128
00:07:17,637 --> 00:07:21,073
I tend to set ¥2,000 as an upper
limit and shop at cheap stores.

129
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:23,973
But I guess that's a mental block.

130
00:07:24,644 --> 00:07:26,578
Expand your horizons some.

131
00:08:29,775 --> 00:08:32,107
You know, I didn't even look at prices.

132
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:34,806
It was all I could do to even go in.

133
00:08:46,893 --> 00:08:48,485
Pathetic...

134
00:08:51,898 --> 00:08:53,058
One more time!

135
00:08:53,733 --> 00:08:55,701
This time I'm looking at prices!

136
00:08:57,904 --> 00:08:58,928
So laughable.

137
00:09:09,749 --> 00:09:13,742
That's expensive,
Kasukabe! I could never!

138
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:15,988
