139
00:09:15,988 --> 00:09:19,515
...but why should a single piece
of clothing need this kind of price!

140
00:09:20,259 --> 00:09:24,320
I can't buy anything expensive
anyway, so I'll go for all-out cheap!

141
00:09:24,830 --> 00:09:27,799
What's bad is giving up
and being all defiant.

142
00:09:28,134 --> 00:09:30,329
No, stop that. Don't panic.

143
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:34,301
No need to buy anything
exorbitant. Just something so-so.

144
00:09:35,007 --> 00:09:38,238
I'll think about tops again
later. Right now, bottoms!

145
00:09:38,744 --> 00:09:39,972
Where're pants...

146
00:09:41,047 --> 00:09:42,537
Are you looking for anything?

147
00:09:42,848 --> 00:09:43,610
Pa...

148
00:09:43,716 --> 00:09:45,183
No! Not pants...

149
00:09:45,685 --> 00:09:46,777
Uh, uh, underwear.

150
00:09:46,852 --> 00:09:47,910
Aw, dammit!

151
00:09:48,688 --> 00:09:49,985
On the second floor.

152
00:09:51,023 --> 00:09:53,355
Th-thanks.

153
00:09:59,932 --> 00:10:00,899
Forget it.

154
00:10:01,233 --> 00:10:04,691
I lose. Total loss. But I guess I tried.

155
00:10:05,037 --> 00:10:06,937
I don't think I've
compared this many prices...

156
00:10:07,006 --> 00:10:09,236
...since dojin shops
during middle school.

157
00:10:15,881 --> 00:10:19,840
Wait. That's right. I'm
shopping the wrong way!

158
00:10:20,052 --> 00:10:21,883
Just comparing prices is meaningless.

159
00:10:22,021 --> 00:10:25,855
The fun level of a game isn't
proportional to its price!

160
00:10:26,859 --> 00:10:28,759
I'll draw my own conclusions!

161
00:10:32,098 --> 00:10:34,191
If I think, "This is nice,"
I'll shell out for it.

162
00:10:34,367 --> 00:10:36,767
I take pride in the things I've chosen.

163
00:10:36,836 --> 00:10:39,896
Adult games, dojinshi,
clothes, it's all the same!

164
00:10:40,072 --> 00:10:43,371
After all, that's what makes me, me!

165
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:44,904
Excuse me!

166
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:49,611
That's what it's all about, Kasukabe!

167
00:10:49,915 --> 00:10:51,348
Not-even-close!

168
00:10:51,751 --> 00:10:53,685
...is what she'll probably say.

169
00:10:56,922 --> 00:10:58,958
Genshiken

170
00:10:58,958 --> 00:11:01,893
Shinjuku Station

171
00:11:14,874 --> 00:11:17,399
Hi, Kasukabe!

172
00:11:23,282 --> 00:11:24,408
Uh, who's he?

173
00:11:24,917 --> 00:11:26,052
A friend of my boyfriend's.

174
00:11:26,052 --> 00:11:28,145
A friend of my boyfriend's.
Ahh, an otaku. I can tell.

175
00:11:28,254 --> 00:11:32,020
What the hell. I knew
she'd just get annoyed.

176
00:11:32,091 --> 00:11:34,958
Just like I said in the first place!

177
00:11:35,027 --> 00:11:37,359
Oh. On your way home, Madarame?

178
00:11:37,830 --> 00:11:39,661
Uh, yeah, I am.

179
00:11:39,732 --> 00:11:40,699
Good timing then.

180
00:11:40,766 --> 00:11:41,858
That's true.

181
00:11:41,967 --> 00:11:43,935
We'll see you later then.

182
00:11:45,938 --> 00:11:47,769
Then I'm headed home too.

183
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:48,840
Wha!

184
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:50,099
You are?

185
00:11:50,943 --> 00:11:52,978
They've got things to do.

186
00:11:52,978 --> 00:11:54,070
Oh...

187
00:11:54,146 --> 00:11:56,205
What? Do you have plans?

188
00:11:56,315 --> 00:11:57,805
No, no, I don't.

189
00:11:58,784 --> 00:12:01,776
Weren't we having a fight?

190
00:12:02,021 --> 00:12:02,715
Huh?

191
00:12:04,156 --> 00:12:04,815
Huh?

192
00:12:05,491 --> 00:12:07,126
