What?

203
00:12:39,492 --> 00:12:43,451
Are you still mad? You could
at least enjoy some food.

204
00:12:44,363 --> 00:12:48,163
You really do seem to
be from another planet.

205
00:12:48,234 --> 00:12:50,794
Me otaku. No understand you.

206
00:12:51,070 --> 00:12:52,332
That again?

207
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:54,933
Kohsaka's not going to mind
this, should he find out.

208
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:58,271
That's because he's from
another galaxy altogether.

209
00:12:58,377 --> 00:13:00,777
How are we handling the bill?

210
00:13:00,846 --> 00:13:03,041
Will we each take one?

211
00:13:03,115 --> 00:13:04,216
Fatty tuna, please.

212
00:13:04,216 --> 00:13:05,649
Fatty tuna, please.
You got it!

213
00:13:05,985 --> 00:13:08,215
Apparently we're not.

214
00:13:09,488 --> 00:13:11,183
Here's your fatty tuna.

215
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:18,195
Where are your new glasses?

216
00:13:18,397 --> 00:13:19,091
Eh?

217
00:13:19,532 --> 00:13:20,829
You paid money for them.

218
00:13:21,233 --> 00:13:22,757
Oh, those...

219
00:13:22,835 --> 00:13:25,804
Weren't they supposed
to go with all that?

220
00:13:28,541 --> 00:13:31,533
I just figured it was
time to buy new stuff.

221
00:13:31,610 --> 00:13:33,874
Sea urchin and steamed abalone, please.

222
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:35,310
What is it? Shirts?

223
00:13:35,548 --> 00:13:37,345
Several things.

224
00:13:38,184 --> 00:13:39,776
Wear them in the clubroom.

225
00:13:39,885 --> 00:13:41,978
Won't you just trash talk them?

226
00:13:43,589 --> 00:13:44,578
Of course.

227
00:13:45,391 --> 00:13:48,792
But the thoughtless stuff you're
wearing now is unspeakable.

228
00:13:48,894 --> 00:13:50,862
It's not even worth a comment.

229
00:13:51,397 --> 00:13:53,365
Geez, you're harsh.

230
00:13:54,266 --> 00:13:57,235
The day you put some thought
into choosing what you wear...

231
00:13:57,303 --> 00:13:59,794
...is the day I grant
you a fair appraisal.

232
00:14:00,206 --> 00:14:02,071
Grant me a fair appraisal, huh?

233
00:14:03,909 --> 00:14:06,309
Want me to order anything for you?

234
00:14:06,378 --> 00:14:10,075
No thanks, I wasted too much money.
I can't spend any on food now.

235
00:14:10,182 --> 00:14:12,207
Here's your steamed abalone.

236
00:14:13,452 --> 00:14:17,320
"Wasted money." I've never
heard you say that before.

237
00:14:17,656 --> 00:14:19,920
When you're from the planet Otaku...

238
00:14:19,992 --> 00:14:23,018
...everything but otaku
materials is a waste of funds.

239
00:14:23,395 --> 00:14:27,422
Again? You keep coming
back to that otaku thing.

240
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:30,034
It doesn't really mean you're an alien.

241
00:14:30,135 --> 00:14:32,603
That doesn't sound like you.

242
00:14:32,938 --> 00:14:34,963
Don't you loathe otaku?

243
00:14:35,474 --> 00:14:40,605
Lest you forget, I'm dating
Kohsaka. That Kohsaka!

244
00:14:41,180 --> 00:14:43,115
Like it or not, I get used to otaku.

245
00:14:43,115 --> 00:14:45,083
Like it or not, I get used to otaku.
I'm guessing not.

246
00:14:45,651 --> 00:14:47,585
I've been making efforts lately too.

247
00:14:47,653 --> 00:14:49,280
Oh? What kind?

248
00:14:49,688 --> 00:14:52,282
Like keeping my distance
when it's anime and game time.

249
00:14:52,524 --> 00:14:55,550
Isn't that you being neglected?

250
00:14:56,262 --> 00:14:57,490
Shut up.

251
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:04,999
Oh, but the other day I
played a game with him some.

252
00:15:10,109 --> 00:15:11,667
Well, how about that?

253
00:15:12,011 --> 00:15:13,945
There's this prince guy.

254
00:15:14,013 --> 00:15:14,945
Prince?

255
00:15:15,147 --> 00:15:17,182
You roll this thing, and
it picks up other things.

256
00:15:17,182 --> 00:15:19,548
Ahh, didn't part two come out recently?

257
00:15:19,685 --> 00:15:24,247
Got me. But it's like, simple and
fun so I played for about an hour.

